The behavior of `reset` has been changed since a loop was added to call setValue for each field. This change was introduced in one of the PRs in `7.55.0-next.8`, specifically [PR#12675](https://github.com/react-hook-form/react-hook-form/pull/12675).

It seems that the changes introduced in #12675 have affected the behavior mentioned in this issue. However, I haven‚Äôt had the time to look into the exact behavior in detail yet. (I suspect there might be some logic that fills in default values when `_fields` is completely empty.)

`7.55.0-next.7`
```ts
// src/logic/createFormControl.ts
const _reset: UseFormReset<TFieldValues> = (
// ...
        _fields = {};
// ...
```

`7.55.0-next.8`
```ts
// src/logic/createFormControl.ts
const _reset: UseFormReset<TFieldValues> = (
// ...
        for (const fieldName of _names.mount) {
          setValue(
            fieldName as FieldPath<TFieldValues>,
            get(values, fieldName),
          );
        }
// ...
```

I agree with @Jarzka‚Äôs opinion that ‚Äúthere should be no functional changes between patch/minor versions.‚Äù
However, at the same time, I find it a bit strange that when a field is intentionally reset with undefined, its value gets replaced with `defaultValue` ‚Äî even if this was the original behavior, it still feels a bit odd.

Here are the options I‚Äôm considering:
	1.	Modify the code so that, on submit, values are filled using defaultValue, just like in versions prior to `7.55.0-next.7`.
	2.	Keep the current behavior introduced in `7.55.0-next.8`.
(Would it help clarify the spec if we add a test case that fails when the behavior reverts to that of versions before `7.55.0-next.7`?)

I‚Äôd like to hear @bluebill1049 's thoughts on this.
